QTERN is not recommended for use to improve glycemic control in patients with type 1 diabetes mellitus [see 

                        WARNINGS AND PRECAUTIONS (5.1)
                     ].

Assess renal function prior to initiation of QTERN therapy and periodically thereafter [see 

                              WARNINGS AND PRECAUTIONS (5.4)

                           ].

Do not coadminister QTERN with strong cytochrome P450 3A4/5 inhibitors (e.g., ketoconazole, atazanavir, clarithromycin, indinavir, itraconazole, nefazodone, nelfinavir, ritonavir, saquinavir, and telithromycin) [see 

                              DRUG INTERACTIONS (7)

                           ].

